[src:api-gateway-patterns/load-balancing-computing] Instead of upgrading the load balancer, which is quite expensive dedicated hardware, it may be cheaper to forgo TLS offload and add a few web servers.
[src:api-gateway-patterns/load-balancing-computing] Also, some server vendors such as Oracle/Sun now incorporate cryptographic acceleration hardware into their CPUs such as the T2000.
[src:api-gateway-patterns/load-balancing-computing] F5 Networks incorporates a dedicated TLS acceleration hardware card in their local traffic manager (LTM) which is used for encrypting and decrypting TLS traffic.
[src:api-gateway-patterns/load-balancing-computing] One clear benefit to TLS offloading in the balancer is that it enables it to do balancing or content switching based on data in the HTTPS request.
[src:api-gateway-patterns/load-balancing-computing] attacks and generally offload work from the servers to a more efficient platform.
[src:api-gateway-patterns/load-balancing-computing] compression available in all modern web browsers.
