[src:api-gateway-patterns/service-oriented-architecture] These services can represent either new applications or just wrappers around existing legacy systems to make them network-enabled.
[src:api-gateway-patterns/service-oriented-architecture] Implementers commonly build SOAs using web services standards.
[src:api-gateway-patterns/service-oriented-architecture] One example is SOAP, which has gained broad industry acceptance after the recommendation of Version 1.2 from the W3C (World Wide Web Consortium) in 2003.
